org.drombler.acp.core.data

Class AbstractDataHandler<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.drombler.acp.core.data.AbstractDataHandler<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the unique key of this data handler
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, LocalContextProvider, DataHandler<T>, org.softsmithy.lib.beans.Bean, org.softsmithy.lib.util.UniqueKeyProvider<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDocumentHandler

    public abstract class AbstractDataHandler<T>
extends Object
implements DataHandler<T>, AutoCloseable
    An abstract DataHandler. It observes registered DataCapabilityProviders and adds the found data capabilities to it's local context. You can use this class as a base class for your own data handler implementations.
    Author:
    puce
